  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" The Central Bureau of Investigation versus Mir Usman @ Ara @ Mir Usman Ali pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_9_1490_1514','2025INSC1155'); ><font size='4'> <strong>THE CENTRAL BUREAU OF INVESTIGATION<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>MIR USMAN @ ARA @ MIR USMAN ALI </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 9 S.C.R. 1490</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1155</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008932025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, K.V. VISWANATHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration When victim herself has stepped into witness box, whether her examination can be done in piecemeal. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 &ndash; s.309 &ndash; Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 &ndash; s.346 &ndash; Examination of instant case, trial court recorded the statement of the victim and thereafter adjourned the matter for further examination by a period of four months &ndash; Whether such prevailing practice can be approved: Held: Section 309 of the Cr.P.C. (now Section 346 of the BNSS, 2023) contains a mandatory<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 22-09-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CRIMINAL) No. 969/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_9_1490_1514','2025INSC1155','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn